NASCP ANC and PMTCT Service Mapping Wed 04 May 2022 16:24

National

Sidebar

Overview

This dashboard was developed to monitor progress with the mapping of antenatal care and PMTCT service delivery sites in Nigeria and displays performance at national, state and local government levels.

The states are grouped by geo-political zone and can be assessed by clicking on the appropriate tab. Each state is allocated a row with its data distributed across three tabs. The names and contents of the tabs are outlined below.

  • LGA Map: Chloropeth map comparing LGA progress with mapping of facilities on health facility register (HFR) in each state. Reports percentage of health facilities in the HFR that have been mapped.

  • Percentage of antenatal facilities on the HFR mapped: Gauge charts showing the percentage of facilities on the health facility register confirmed as providing antenatal care presented in each local government area of the state.

  • Number of antenatal service delivery sites mapped: Table with five columns with self-explanatory headings.

Notes on State LGA Maps

18 LGAs in 8 states do not have a health facility that provides antenatal care on the National Health Facility Register (HFR) maintained by the Federal Ministry of Health. These LGAs are shaded grey. The 8 states and 18 LGAs are outlined below.

State LGA with no ANC facility on HFR
Abia Ikwuano
Akwa Ibom Eastern Obolo, Esit Eket, Ibesikpo Asutan, Ibiono Ibom, Okobo, Uruan
Borno Guzamala, Kukawa, Marte, Mobbar
Imo Oguta
Kaduna Igabi
Rivers Andoni
Sokoto Rabah, Sokoto South, Tangaza
Taraba Gashaka

The data displayed on this dashboard is collected and reported by local government teams using a standardized data collection tool on their smart phones. It is updated in the morning (0700-0900) and late afternoon (1600-1800).

For further information, please contact the National Coordinator, NASCP. Email: nga.nascp@gmail.com
